stylometry: Data mining is when you sort through high masses of data so that you can find the information that is useful to you. You can use statistical tools (such as cluster analysis) so that you can reveal trends, patterns, or relationships in the large amounts of data. It is important because in business you will always have huge amounts of data at any one time, but you will not need to use all of it when you are trying to solve a specific problem or retrieve specific stats for a report or something. So data mining allows you to only pull out the specific data related to the problem you are trying to solve and saves you the time or seaching through it all by hand.
